<item>
            <title>[HBASE-5303] Separate out rows into multiple files during compaction for better block cache utilization</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5303</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This seems odd at first sight, a compaction is supposed to reduce the number of files. But there is great advantage to creating hbase blocks where adjacent keys are accessed together. One approach would be to make compaction write out hot-rows into one file and the cold-rows into another file. This increases the efficiency of the block cache because only the blocks in the hot-rows file will most frequently be populated in the block cache.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
